President Obama has declared a state of emergency in Missouri due to a severe winter storm that began on January 31, 2011. This declaration allows the Federal Emergency Management Agency (FEMA) to coordinate disaster relief efforts and provide assistance to the affected areas. FEMA is authorized to mobilize resources and equipment to help alleviate the impacts of the emergency. Emergency protective measures will be funded at 75 percent by the federal government. Elizabeth Turner has been named as the Federal Coordinating Officer for recovery operations in the affected area. For more information, contact FEMA at (202) 646-3272.